Sample JSON Data used to create form,

form = {
name: "TestForm",
fields:
    [
      {type: "text", name: "firstname", label: "Name" , required: true, data:""},
      {type: "radio", name: "color_id", label: "Colors" , options:[{id: 1, name: "orange"},{id: 2, name: "pink"},{id: 3, name: "gray"},{id: 4, name: "cyan"}], required: true, data:""},
      {type: "email", name: "emailUser", label: "Email" , required: true, data:""},
      {type: "text", name: "city", label: "City" , required: true, data:""},
      {type: "password", name: "pass", label: "Password" , minPassword: 6, required: true, data:""},
      {type: "select", name: "programmer_id", label: "Programmer" , options:[{name: "Sagun"},{name: "Ruraj"},{name: "Sushan"},{name: "Subigya"}], required: true, data:""},
      {type: "checkbox", name: "language_id", label: "Programming Language" , options:[{id: 1, name: "JAVA"},{id: 2, name: "Python"},{id: 3, name: "C++"},{id: 4, name: "Scala"}], required: true, data:""}
    ]
}


Creating form from JSON,

<form name="{{form.name}}">
    <dn-input ng-repeat="field in form.fields"></dn-input>
</form>